The condominium plat may consist of one or more sheets and shall contain at least the following particulars:
The name of the condominium;
A boundary survey of the property described in the declaration showing the location of all buildings on the property and the physical markings at the corners of the property;
Diagrammatic floor plans of each building on the property which show the measured dimensions, floor area, and location of each unit in it. Common elements shall be shown diagrammatically to the extent feasible; and
The elevation, or average elevation in case of minor variances, above sea level, or from a fixed known point, of the upper and lower boundaries of each unit delineated on the condominium plat.

section.section:
The court may reform the condominium plat to correct the error or omission as the court considers appropriate, if:
The council of unit owners gives notice of the filing of the petition to each mortgagee and unit owner within 15 days of filing;
The council of unit owners files an affidavit with the court stating that the conditions of subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph have been met;
The council of unit owners proves, by a preponderance of the evidence, that there is an error or omission as provided in subparagraph (i) of this paragraph;
Any mortgagee with an interest in the condominium is permitted to intervene in the proceedings upon filing a motion to intervene as provided in the Maryland Rules;
The reformation does not substantially impair the property rights of any unit owner or mortgagee; and
The court issues an order of reformation.
